# Windows + D: — Carbon WMS dev disk policy (all agents)

## Why

Without explicit env, **Flutter / Gradle / JVM** use **`%TEMP%` on C:**, **Pub** under **`%LOCALAPPDATA%\Pub\Cache`**, **Gradle** under **`%USERPROFILE%\.gradle`** — C: can fill and the machine becomes unstable. **`_carbon_wms_d_env.ps1` only applies when dot-sourced** (e.g. `build-apk.ps1`, `env-d-drive.ps1`); **Cursor and raw `flutter` commands often do not.**

## What we did / require

1. **One-time (per Windows user):** from `mobile/carbon_wms`, run **`.\scripts\install-user-build-env-on-d.ps1`**. Sets **User** env: **`TEMP`/`TMP`/`TMPDIR`**, **`PUB_CACHE`**, **`GRADLE_USER_HOME`**, **`XDG_*`** under **`D:\CarbonWmsTooling\`**. User must **fully restart Cursor** so new terminals inherit vars.

2. **Per build / session:** **`build-apk.ps1`** or dot-source **`.\scripts\env-d-drive.ps1`** before Android Studio from that shell — uses **`_carbon_wms_d_env.ps1`** (repo **`.tools\`** or **`D:\CarbonWmsTooling\`** if repo path has **spaces**).

3. **Paths with spaces:** use junction **`D:\cwm`** → clone; work from **`D:\cwm\mobile\carbon_wms`**; **`android/local.properties`** uses **no-space** paths. See **`mobile/carbon_wms/README.md`**.

4. **Docker Desktop (local Windows):** keep app + WSL data on **D:** (`--installation-dir`, `--wsl-default-data-root`) so Docker does not consume C:. **Coolify** = server-side; separate from this.

5. **Flutter SDK:** Prefer **`D:\flutter`** (stable zip on **D:**). Workspace **`.vscode/settings.json`** sets **`dart.flutterSdkPath`** for Dart/Flutter extensions. **`install-user-build-env-on-d.ps1`** sets **`FLUTTER_ROOT`** and **`Path`** when **`D:\flutter`** exists. Fallback: **`<repo>/.tools/flutter`**.

6. **APK builds:** **`.\scripts\build-apk.ps1`**; use **`-SkipTests`** if **`flutter test`** / native hooks block release. Canonical output: **`D:\CarbonWmsRelease\CarbonWMS V{pubspec}.apk`**.

Full prose: **`AGENTS.md`** (Windows + D: section). Handheld details: **`mobile/carbon_wms/README.md`**.
